    "description": "<i>“Are you lost?”<br><br>“I don’t think so? I mean, the way back to town is pretty straightforward.”</i><br>...<br><br>Welcome to Hope, where most of the residents ironically don't have high hopes for their future.<br><br>The player plays as John Doe, just another life in the little town of Hope whose luck has hit rock bottom. However, when John meets a hermit living outside of town, he gradually learns to put his life together.<br><br>Explore the town. Talk to the residents. Everyone has a story to tell.<br><br>Work. Or not.<br><br>Save money. Go broke paying rent.<br><br>Find love. Or be alone.<br><br>Buy a house and nice furniture. Or dream about it.<br><br>Help John reach his full potential.  Or give up on John forever.<br><br>Happiness can be found right around the corner. If John only knows where to look (or have someone point it out to him). This is a game about hope and, ultimately, what it really means to live and be happy.",
